hpnicfAcl.description: ACL management information base for managing devices that support access control list and packet filtering.

RuleAction.name: RuleAction
RuleAction.description: The value of rule's action. permit: The packet matching the rule will be permitted to forward. deny: The packet matching the rule will be denied.

CounterClear.description: cleared: Reset the value of the rule's counter. nouse: 'nouse' will be returned when getting.

AddressFlag.name: AddressFlag
AddressFlag.description: Address flag to select IPv6 Address. Default value is 'invalid'. t64SrcAddrPre64DestAddrPre(1): The mean of the enumeration 't64SrcAddrPre64DestAddrPre' is that system gets the 64 bits prefix of source address and the 64 bits prefix of destination address. t64SrcAddrPre64DestAddrSuf(2): The mean of the enumeration 't64SrcAddrPre64DestAddrSuf' is that system gets the 64 bits prefix of source address and the 64 bits suffix of destination address. t64SrcAddrSuf64DestAddrPre(3): The mean of the enumeration 't64SrcAddrSuf64DestAddrPre' is that system gets the 64 bits suffix of source address and the 64 bits prefix of destination address. t64SrcAddrSuf64DestAddrSuf(4): The mean of the enumeration 't64SrcAddrSuf64DestAddrSuf' is that system gets the 64 bits suffix of source address and the 64 bits suffix of destination address. t128SourceAddress(5): The mean of the enumeration 't128SourceAddress' is that system gets the 128 bits of source address. t128DestinationAddress(6): The mean of the enumeration 't128SourceAddress' is that system gets the 128 bits of destination address.

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedRuleIndex.description: The rule index of advanced acl group. As a Simple ACL group, the value of this object must be 0. As an Advanced ACL group, the value of this object is ranging from 0 to 65534.

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedAct.description: The action of advanced acl rule.

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedProtocol.name: hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedProtocol

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedSrcAddrType.description: The IP addresses type of IP pool.

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedSrcAny.name: hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedSrcAny
hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedSrcAny.description: The flag of matching any IP address.

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedDestAny.description: The flag of matching any IP address.

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedPrecedence.name: hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedPrecedence

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedTos.description: The value of IP-packet's TOS. <0-15> Value of TOS(type of service) max-reliability Match packets with max reliable TOS(2) max-throughput Match packets with max throughput TOS(4) min-delay Match packets with min delay TOS(8) min-monetary-cost Match packets with min monetary cost TOS(1) normal Match packets with normal TOS(0)

hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedDscp.name: hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedDscp
hpnicfAclIPAclAdvancedDscp.description: The value of DSCP of IP packet.

hpnicfAclResourceUsageTable.name: hpnicfAclResourceUsageTable
hpnicfAclResourceUsageTable.description: The table shows ACL resource usage information. Support for resource types that are denoted by hpnicfAclResourceType object varies with products. If a type is not supported, the corresponding row for the type will not be instantiated in this table.

hpnicfAclResourceUsageEntry.name: hpnicfAclResourceUsageEntry
hpnicfAclResourceUsageEntry.description: Each row contains a brief description of the resource type, a port range associated with the chip, total, reserved, and configured amount of resource of this type, the percent of resource that has been allocated, and so on.

hpnicfAclResourceChassis.name: hpnicfAclResourceChassis
hpnicfAclResourceChassis.description: The chassis number. On a centralized or distributed device, the value for this node is always zero.

hpnicfAclResourceSlot.name: hpnicfAclResourceSlot
hpnicfAclResourceSlot.description: The slot number. On a centralized device, the value for this node is always zero.

hpnicfAclResourceChip.name: hpnicfAclResourceChip
hpnicfAclResourceChip.description: The chip number. On a single chip device, the value for this node is always zero.

hpnicfAclPortRange.name: hpnicfAclPortRange
hpnicfAclPortRange.description: The port range associated with the chip. Commas are used to separate multiple port ranges, for example, Ethernet1/2 to Ethernet1/12, Ethernet1/31 to Ethernet1/48.

hpnicfAclResourceTotal.name: hpnicfAclResourceTotal
hpnicfAclResourceTotal.description: Total TCAM entries of the resource type.

hpnicfAclResourceReserved.name: hpnicfAclResourceReserved
hpnicfAclResourceReserved.description: The amount of reserved TCAM entries of the resource type.

hpnicfAclResourceConfigured.name: hpnicfAclResourceConfigured
hpnicfAclResourceConfigured.description: The amount of configured TCAM entries of the resource type.

hpnicfAclResourceUsagePercent.name: hpnicfAclResourceUsagePercent
hpnicfAclResourceUsagePercent.description: The percent of TCAM entries that have been used for this resource type.

hpnicfAclResourceTypeDescription.name: hpnicfAclResourceTypeDescription
hpnicfAclResourceTypeDescription.description: The description of this resource type.

hpnicfPfilterDefaultAction.name: hpnicfPfilterDefaultAction
hpnicfPfilterDefaultAction.description: The default action of packet filter. By default, the packet filter permits packets that do not match any ACL rule to pass.

hpnicfPfilterProcessingStatus.name: hpnicfPfilterProcessingStatus
hpnicfPfilterProcessingStatus.description: This object shows the status of the system when applying packet filter. It is forbidden to set or read in hpnicfAclPacketFilterObjects MIB module when the value is processing.

hpnicfPfilterApplyTable.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyTable
hpnicfPfilterApplyTable.description: A table of packet filter application. It's not supported to set default action on an entity, but supported to enable hardware count of default action on an entity.

hpnicfPfilterApplyObjType.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyObjType
hpnicfPfilterApplyObjType.description: The object type of packet filter application. interface: Apply an ACL to the interface to filter packets. vlan: Apply an ACL to the VLAN to filter packets. global: Apply an ACL globally to filter packets.

hpnicfPfilterApplyObjIndex.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyObjIndex
hpnicfPfilterApplyObjIndex.description: The object ID of packet filter application. Interface: interface index, equal to ifIndex VLAN: VLAN ID, 1..4094 Global: 0

hpnicfPfilterApplyDirection.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyDirection
hpnicfPfilterApplyDirection.description: The direction of packet filter application.

hpnicfPfilterApplyAclType.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyAclType
hpnicfPfilterApplyAclType.description: ACL Type: IPv4, IPv6, default action. Take default action as a special ACL group.

hpnicfPfilterApplyAclIndex.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyAclIndex
hpnicfPfilterApplyAclIndex.description: The ACL group index. Basic type: 2000..2999 Advanced type: 3000..3999 MAC type: 4000..4999 User type: 5000..5999 Default action type: 0

hpnicfPfilterApplyHardCount.name: hpnicfPfilterApplyHardCount
hpnicfPfilterApplyHardCount.description: Hardware count flag. true: enable hardware count false: disable hardware count

hpnicfPfilterApplySequence.name: hpnicfPfilterApplySequence
hpnicfPfilterApplySequence.description: The configure sequence of packet filter application.

hpnicfPfilterAclGroupRunInfoTable.name: hpnicfPfilterAclGroupRunInfoTable

hpnicfPfilterAclGroupRunInfoEntry.name: hpnicfPfilterAclGroupRunInfoEntry
hpnicfPfilterAclGroupRunInfoEntry.description: ACL group running information entry for packet filtering.

hpnicfPfilterRunApplyObjType.name: hpnicfPfilterRunApplyObjType
hpnicfPfilterRunApplyObjType.description: The object type of packet filter application. interface: Apply an ACL to the interface to filter packets. vlan: Apply an ACL to the VLAN to filter packets. global: Apply an ACL globally to filter packets.

hpnicfPfilterRunApplyObjIndex.name: hpnicfPfilterRunApplyObjIndex
hpnicfPfilterRunApplyObjIndex.description: The object ID of packet filter application. Interface: interface index, equal to ifIndex VLAN: VLAN ID, 1..4094 Global: 0

hpnicfPfilterRunApplyDirection.name: hpnicfPfilterRunApplyDirection
hpnicfPfilterRunApplyDirection.description: The direction of packet filter application.

hpnicfPfilterRunApplyAclType.name: hpnicfPfilterRunApplyAclType
hpnicfPfilterRunApplyAclType.description: ACL Type: IPv4, IPv6, default action. Take default action as a special ACL group.

hpnicfPfilterRunApplyAclIndex.name: hpnicfPfilterRunApplyAclIndex
hpnicfPfilterRunApplyAclIndex.description: The ACL group index. Basic type: 2000..2999 Advanced type: 3000..3999 MAC type: 4000..4999 User type: 5000..5999 MAC default action: 1 IPv4 default action: 2 IPv6 default action: 3

hpnicfPfilterAclGroupStatus.name: hpnicfPfilterAclGroupStatus
hpnicfPfilterAclGroupStatus.description: The status of ACL group applied. success: ACL applied successfully on all slots failed: failed to apply ACL on all slots partialSuccess: failed to apply ACL on some slots

hpnicfPfilterAclGroupCountStatus.name: hpnicfPfilterAclGroupCountStatus
hpnicfPfilterAclGroupCountStatus.description: The status of enabling hardware count. If hardware count is not enabled, it returns success. success: enable hardware count successfully on all slots failed: failed to enable hardware count on all slots partialSuccess: failed to enable hardware count on some slots

hpnicfPfilterAclRuleRunInfoTable.name: hpnicfPfilterAclRuleRunInfoTable

hpnicfPfilterAclRuleStatus.name: hpnicfPfilterAclRuleStatus
hpnicfPfilterAclRuleStatus.description: The status of rule application. success: rule applied successfully on all slots failed: failed to apply rule on all slots partialSuccess: failed to apply rule on some slots

hpnicfPfilterAclRuleCountStatus.name: hpnicfPfilterAclRuleCountStatus
hpnicfPfilterAclRuleCountStatus.description: The status of enabling rule's hardware count. If hardware count is not enabled, it returns success. success: enable hardware count successfully on all slots failed: failed to enable hardware count on all slots partialSuccess: failed to enable hardware count on some slots

hpnicfPfilterStatisticSumTable.name: hpnicfPfilterStatisticSumTable
hpnicfPfilterStatisticSumTable.description: A table of ACL rule's sum statistics information, accumulated by all entity application on all slots.

hpnicfPfilterStatisticSumEntry.name: hpnicfPfilterStatisticSumEntry
hpnicfPfilterStatisticSumEntry.description: ACL rule's sum statistics information entry.

hpnicfPfilterSumAclIndex.name: hpnicfPfilterSumAclIndex
hpnicfPfilterSumAclIndex.description: The ACL group index. Basic type: 2000..2999 Advanced type: 3000..3999 MAC type: 4000..4999 User type: 5000..5999

hpnicfPfilterSumRuleMatchPackets.name: hpnicfPfilterSumRuleMatchPackets
hpnicfPfilterSumRuleMatchPackets.description: The sum number of packets matched the ACL rule.
